<author><name><![CDATA[w7n]]></name></author>
<updated>2013-10-01T18:54:11-07:00</updated>
<published>2013-10-01T18:54:11-07:00</published>
<id>http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=10551&amp;p=118852#p118852</id>
<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=10551&amp;p=118852#p118852"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[So... How do I know if a mapper actually supports 4-screen?]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=10551&amp;p=118852#p118852"><![CDATA[
A chip supports 4-screen if it has additional VRAM. But such info(whether a chip has VRAM or not) is not included in the NESDev wiki.<br /><br />I'm currently using Mapper 85(Konami VRC7) in a hacking project. The 2 original games which used VRC7 didn't use 4-screen at all, and the nametable mirroring control bits only support H-, V-, and 1-screen.<br />So does VRC7 actually support 4-screen mirroring? Emulation for VRC7 4-screen mirroring on Nestopia works fine, but I'm still curious.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=5994">w7n</a> — Tue Oct 01, 2013 6:54 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
